      "id": "LN_01",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Skip Counting on a Number Line",
      "content": "A number line starts at 0. Each jump is the same size. To find 3 × 4, make 3 jumps of 4: 0 → 4 → 8 → 12. You land on 12, so 3 × 4 = 12. The number you land on is always the product.",
